o powerful.&quot; Then they nerfed it. <br>  <br> Hmm....with enough Donal Bps...... <br>  <br> They nerfed it again. I believe FoH showed them chain healing from a string of BPs was still infinite life for a tank. <br>  <br> BUT they didn't stop there. They wanted to change CH but it was too late in the life cycle of EQ to remove the spell. So what do you do? You change the way monsters react to it. <br>  <br> 1) Give it an AE aggro <br>  <br> 2) Give it a really high cap (aggro) <br>  <br> The idea behind that is to discourage it's use in encounters. <br>  <br> So far, from &quot;My&quot; gameplay, I've found that I rarely CH in an exp group. Typically, I group with friends or guildmates. People whom we know one another's play styles and abilities. <br>  <br> Good steady pulls and a nice flow of blue in my exp bar. With good pulling and teamwork, there's plenty of time to toss a Cel healing and remedy in place of a CH. Or just several Remedies if multiple people suffer from a damage shield or AE effect. <br>  <br> Now what's different is an epic/uber encounter. <br>  <br> These mobs have a hug aggro chart first of all. That's good. Typically, the largest force that will be sent against a mob will be 40 people (Velk or Gorenaire.) You step in aggro range and &quot;ding&quot; you're somewhere on that aggro chart. That's good as well. <br>  <br> What's bad? <br>  <br> You CH one tank and get summoned. Now in the exp group, you were 6 people facing a mob that doubled for 100-200. This epic mob doubles or quads for 300-850. <br>  <br> So when I see nerf-defenders on whineplay say &quot;Oh I only got hit for one round by a krup&quot; I feel like cramming a Donal boot in their arse. Give that Krup wings, make him bigger, and change his name to Gorenaire and then tell me about the round that they didn't mind. <br>  <br> Under what circumstances do you reasonably think a cleric should out-aggro 10 warriors, 3 rogues, a score of casters, and pets? That's what VI didn't think about. The epic encounter that they don't have a reasonable means of testing since the folks on the test server don't raid anywhere near the efficiency of a more established server like Povar. <br>  <br> Velious is all about Uber Guilds. It's all about &quot;Kill that dragon, kill that giant, kill the dorf king.&quot; The gear the entire expansion on melee efficiency supported by CH. (Mobs hit harder and have Far more hp than the same mob in Kunark.) <br>  <br> I think they knew they would have to boost Shaman and druid healing to compensate. Bad timing caused them to boost secondary healer efficacy while reducing primary healer ability. This makes the nerf look far worse than if they would have boosted the other classes and HELD OFF the nerf while testing the damned thing. <br>  <br> Now that I know I can generate more aggro than an entire raiding party, easily, I'm curious to see what lies ahead. <br> <p></p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span><div class="SignatureText">**** <br> 1) Find Corpse <br> 2) Check Pockets for loose change <br> 3) Use rez stick <br>  <br> </div></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23lockedtopic">Locked Topic</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=9445454" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=6823">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=6823">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/RombusMindspire?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">RombusMindspire</a>&nbsp;<a href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23stars"><img align=absmiddle src=http://media.ign.com/boardimages/star.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="236 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & C